Our Sensitive Protection baby diapers are made without fragrances, lotions, or chlorine bleaching, and use only FSC Certified, sustainably sourced wood pulp that’s gentle on our planet’s forests. Wrapped in Seventh Generation’s softest, best diaper yet—the future looks good on your baby.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for sensitive skin
reviews.reviewText: Love these diapers. My baby has very sensitive skin and these don't seem to bother him at all. Will be using this brand again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My daughter has had allergy issues with a few other diaper brands not with this one. We also have been happy with Honest diapers which are more absorbent and have prettier designs but overall comparable. I liked Seven generation diapers and would recommend them.

reviews.reviewText: These diapers are great but they are too big. I with size 3 was in normal stock. Seems like there are a lot of 2022 babies bc this size is hard to find depending on the brand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Chemical free diapers for sensitive skin
reviews.reviewText: Update 2020:We've been using these diapers exclusively for our daughter for the past 2 years and so far I've absolutely loved every single minute of it. But their "new line" came out, "ocean future", well... Ocean is right because so far she's been using it for a week and every single night, has leaked through it. It just won't last through the night.I'm conflicted because my daughter has sensitive skin so I can't switch her to pampers/huggies. And I JUST received a big pack of these diapers that's supposed to last me for the month! 🙄😔😑! I feel like I just wasted my money!Original post:I love these diapers!! They are VERY durable!!! The band is so hardcore, in the 4 months we've been using them, I've only had 1 diaper band rip! (Vs the at least once a week with pampers and Huggies).My only regret is that I wasn't doing the subscribe and save until now! :(The diapers are wonderful and they are the ONLY thing I use for my daughter!I definitely recommend it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Still leaves baby’s scin wet despite absorbency
reviews.reviewText: I really wanted to like them. I love how soft they are and much thinner they are than other brands. They do run a bit smaller but that was ok with me because my baby is petite. But even though they are very absorbent, they don't take away the wetness from my baby's skin like other brands do. They also sometimes tend to get loose as time goes by. It doesn't happen with every diaper in the packet though so I don't really know that it's on purpose. They never fell off or anything but that was always one of my fears. I went back to the brand I was using and my baby was back to being a bit more comfortable than she had been these past couple weeks that we’ve been trying these diapers out. I am still very happy we got to try these out because they do have lots of potential. I wish they would have worked for us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Both Environmentally and baby friendly
reviews.reviewText: These diapers have treated us well! They are comfy, work well, soft and cute. Aside from amazon mama bear, they are usually the cheapest, semi-environmentally-friendly diaper. We have used these for about a year and tried mama bear - we like these better despite the slightly higher cost. We had less issue with diaper rash and less issue with any leakage. These seem to be better fitted to our kiddo’s shape. I also don’t like the waist on the mama bears (although if you like huggies you might feel otherwise). I appreciate that seventh generation set the standard that amazon has to beat and, in my opinion, they haven’t done it yet. So I will continue to fund seventh generation in hopes that they keep innovating!For further info: We’ve gone thru 6 brands in total and some cloth diapers bc I bargain hunt. Bambo and babyganics but I like these better. New Bambos are outrageously expensive and I just can’t justify it. Babyganics feel like they are made of cardboard and i had to crumple them before putting them on my baby to soften them up. Pampers were great for our newborn but pretty awful for the environment and didn’t offer anything that seventh generation doesn’t. And I didn’t like the huggies at all since they’d leak on our baby and leach chemicals in the landfill.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Soft and gentle but not very absorbent
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these diapers recently because my infants seem to have developed a sensitivity so most other diapers.They are very soft and don't seem to irritate the infants skin. But they do need changed fairly frequently. Not really great all night diapers. They also do not hold in poo very well. There have been a few incidents.Also there have been a couple times when the diaper gel/stuff leaked out.So if you need gentle diapers these are good but beware you may need to change them more than many other brands of diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Favorite Diaper Brand
reviews.reviewText: We love the seventh generation brand. We use this brand as diapers on our third baby now. We noticed some brands are made for chubby babies and others are more for skinny babies. The seventh generation diapers are so super stretchy, they fit on every baby! And they might seem thin, but they are just as absorbent as the thicker and more fluffy diapers! And I like that they are thinner than their competitors, because that way I get a lot more diapers stored in the drawer! That the absorbency is just like with others makes me think that the thicker and more fluffy diapers from competitors have material for no reason, which is a waste of resources.
